avalan for Debian
=================

This package installs the Avalan SDK and the `avalan` / `avl`
command-line tools without pulling in heavyweight or
hardware-specific dependencies. A few features need extra setup,
described below.

Playwright browsers
-------------------

Playwright browsers are NOT installed and no browser is pulled as a
dependency. Browser-using Avalan features (web automation, scraping,
etc.) will fail until you provide one. Two supported paths:

  1. System browser (recommended on shared hosts):

       sudo apt install chromium      # or: sudo apt install firefox

     then set `PLAYWRIGHT_BROWSERS_PATH=/usr/bin` and pass the system
     executable via Playwright's `executable_path` API.

  2. Playwright-managed browsers (per-user):

       playwright install

     binaries land under `~/.cache/ms-playwright/`.

Either way, the .deb stays small and `apt install avalan` never
downloads a browser in the background.

Heavyweight extras
------------------

Features that depend on GPU/Apple/CUDA stacks, large model bundles,
or hardware-specific libraries are not in the .deb. The upstream
extras that are out of scope: local, vision, audio, memory, mlx,
apple, nvidia, vllm, quantization, ds4, secrets, translation.

To use them, create a virtualenv and install with pip on top of the
system Avalan install:

    python3 -m venv ~/.avalan/venv
    source ~/.avalan/venv/bin/activate
    pip install "avalan[local]"        # or [vision], [audio], ...

API keys
--------

Vendor backends (OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, AWS) read their
credentials from environment variables at runtime. The package does
not configure them — set them in your shell, .env, systemd unit, or
secret store as appropriate.

